3.6 Additional Key Concepts & Jargon for Understanding This Paper

ğŸ“Œ Key Terms Explained Simply:

ğŸ”¹ Graph Convolutional Neural Network (GCN): A deep learning technique specialized for processing graph-structured data like 5G network topologies.

ğŸ”¹ Differentiated Weight GCN (DWGCN): An enhanced GCN that assigns different importance (weights) to network nodes to improve AI predictions.

ğŸ”¹ Maximal Weight Matching: A mathematical technique that ensures the AI-selected VNF placements are feasible and optimized.

ğŸ”¹ Transfer Learning: A machine learning method that uses knowledge from pre-trained models to reduce the need for large datasets.

ğŸ”¹ SFC Mapping Cost: The total network resource consumption (bandwidth, CPU, memory) required to deploy and maintain an SFC.

ğŸ”¹ Time Efficiency: The speed at which AI can compute an optimal VNF placement decision.


